## How `flow` drives this project (the mechanism, not just the contract)

Three layers, in order of decreasing strength:

### 1. Auto-loading rules (deterministic — fire on path matches every relevant edit)

Plugin-shipped rules (live at `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/rules/`; auto-load when `flow@flow` is enabled):

| Rule | Loads on path-match | Enforces |
|---|---|---|
| `general.md` | `**/*` (every edit) | Workflow discipline, scope, autonomy guardrails, "never merge" |
| `plan-discipline.md` | `**/plan.md` | Required plan fields (mode, goal, scope in/out, spec-walk, confidence verdicts) + LOW = automatic human gate |
| `documentation.md` | `**/{history,feedback,plan,roadmap,spec}.md` | Format rules (history entry shape, FB-XXXX entry shape, memory entry shape) |
| `exploration.md` | `src/**`, `app/**`, `lib/**`, `packages/**` | Grep this project's `roadmap.md § Exploration` for `Surfaces when:` triggers matching the file you're editing |

Project-side rules (live at `.claude/rules/`; this project owns them):

| Rule | Loads on | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `safety.md` | safety-critical paths declared in its `paths:` frontmatter — see that file for the current list | Read recent git log before modifying; never silently downgrade error handling; flag SAFETY in commits + history.md |
| `ui.md` (UI projects only) | UI file edits | Read `design-language.md` first; use tokens, not raw values; WCAG 2.1 AA baseline |
| `dev-server.md` (UI projects only) | UI file edits | Surface dev URL via `/link` after UI changes |

When you edit a file whose path matches any of these `paths:` globs, Claude Code automatically loads the rule into the agent's context. **This is the load-bearing enforcement layer** — even if a skill is skipped, the rules still fire.

### 2. Skill auto-invocation (probabilistic — fires on description match)

`/flow:*` skills auto-trigger when phrases in their `description:` field match the conversation. Examples:

- After writing a plan → `/flow:critique-plan` (description: "Critique the most recent plan for scope drift, spec violation, internal incoherence")
- After completing implementation → `/flow:staff-review` (description: "Reviews the workspace's pending changes from four parallel staff-level perspectives")
- After saying "ship it" / "wrap this up" → `/flow:ship`

Not guaranteed to fire — model invocation is probabilistic. Type `/flow:<skill-name>` explicitly when you want certainty.

### 3. `/flow:ship` Step 1.0 assumption surface (after-the-fact — fires at ship time)

When you invoke `/flow:ship`, the pipeline's first action prints the workflow steps it ASSUMES already ran (Step 2 `/flow:critique-plan`, Step 6 `/simplify`, Step 7 `/flow:staff-review`). This is **informational only — doesn't gate** — but it surfaces silent skips so you notice the short-circuit at ship time rather than weeks later. Even on docs-only PRs, the discipline holds; see `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/docs/workflow.md` Step 2 + Step 6 "even on docs-only" notes.

After the assumption surface, `/flow:ship` runs hard pre-flight gates (Step 1a stale-base, Step 1.5 gh+jq fail-fast, etc.) that DO block on failure.

### What's NOT enforced today (honest gaps)

- **No Stop hook** that fails a session if `/flow:critique-plan` was skipped on a plan. The user can technically execute against an un-critiqued plan. Workflow.md's "Run on EVERY plan" qualifier captures the discipline, but enforcement is the auto-loading rules + `/flow:ship` Step 1.0 surface, not a hard hook. v1.x autonomous-routines work will add Stop hooks for this class.
- **No scope-check on Edit|Write** outside a plan's declared `files_touched`. Same v1.x scope.

## Docs

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `core-docs/spec.md` | Product vision, problem, solution, feature table, open questions |
| `core-docs/plan.md` | Current focus, active work items, handoff notes |
| `core-docs/roadmap.md` | Horizons (Now / Next / Later) + § Exploration |
| `core-docs/history.md` | Per-PR decision log: what + why + tradeoffs |
| `core-docs/feedback.md` | User feedback synthesized to rules (FB-XXXX) |
| `core-docs/design-language.md` | (UI projects) Tokens, axioms, components, motion — read before any UI change |

## Quality bar

- **Polished over partial.** Every visible control does its job. Wire-vs-defer: if the gap is < 1 day, wire it; else remove the visible affordance and capture in roadmap.
- **Scope expansion is additive.** Ship the smallest polished form first.
- **No false affordances.** A button that doesn't work is a bug equivalent to a crash.

## Verify setup

In a Claude Code session at this project's root:

```
/flow:doctor
```

PASS / FAIL / WARN per check. Each FAIL prints the fix command. If `/flow:doctor` doesn't surface in your session, the plugin isn't enabled — re-run `/plugin install flow@flow` or check `.claude/settings.json`'s `enabledPlugins` entry.

